 <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Letter of Apology regarding LGuK Raid 1/25/03</span><hr size=1> Sorry raid didn't go as planned.  Problems at home coupled with confusion during the attempted raid led to me not being able to lead at 100%.  Also, this was my first raid that ive led, and I hope that even tho I didnt get to see you guys through, you had a good time. Barl, some of the fribbits attacked without warning, and im sorry ya took the faction hits, but they cam be fixed down in LGuk killing undead fribbits.  Rin, sorry if ya thought i yelled at ya but stepmother was breathing down my neck forcing me to get off the comp while she was aslo yelling at my lil sisters to clean the basement up.<br>
<br>
Hopefully, this hasen't turned everyone off to raids, as I do plan on trying to ressurect that Unrest raid so we can <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>learn</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> raiding.  Its something every guild goes through.  We just need to pull a few like that...it may sound boring and slow, but....I learned a lot from this raid, and I hope to use that knowledge to lead better raids in the future.  Hope you get some loot annd plat, good luck in there, I know everyone will do well.<br>
<br>
 Aram Wolfpaw<br>
